&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Senior Product Manager to lead one of the most ambitious bets at CoLab: building AI-powered review systems that help engineering teams identify issues before they become expensive downstream problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team owns AutoReview — the capabilities that proactively surface risks, patterns, missing context, and engineering concerns across complex design workflows. The goal isn’t to replace engineers. It’s to help them make better decisions, faster, using the collective knowledge generated across every review inside CoLab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a difficult product problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be operating at the intersection of AI, engineering workflows, enterprise trust, and product usability. The hard part isn’t simply building AI features — it’s building products technical teams actually trust enough to use in high-stakes environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with Engineering, Design, ML/AI teams, and customers to determine how to create tools that deliver real customer value. Some weeks you’ll be deep in workflow discovery with customers. Other weeks you’ll be making prioritization calls across model capabilities, UX tradeoffs, and platform constraints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires strong product judgment. There’s no playbook for this category yet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You won’t thrive here if you’re looking for highly predictable roadmaps, lightweight consumer problems, or environments where Product simply coordinates delivery. We need someone who can bring structure to ambiguity, challenge assumptions, and help the team make hard decisions quickly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The average person might think this role sounds overwhelming. If it sounds energizing, you’ll probably fit right in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re deeply curious about how complex systems work — both technical systems and human ones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You know how to navigate ambiguity without creating chaos. You can hold a strong product perspective while staying highly collaborative with technical teams. You ask thoughtful questions, seek signals quickly, and care deeply about whether customers genuinely trust and adopt what you build.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You likely have experience building technical B2B SaaS products, especially products involving AI-assisted workflows, automation, recommendations, or decision support systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You probably won’t enjoy this role if:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You need fully defined requirements before moving work forward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You treat AI as a branding exercise instead of a product problem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You avoid technical complexity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You optimize for shipping volume, customer trust and product quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About CoLab&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At CoLab, we help mechanical engineering teams bring life-changing products to market years sooner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CoLab is the AI platform for driving stronger engineering decisions. Every design review in CoLab builds a knowledge repository of design feedback, decisions, and lessons learned - which AI agents draw from to flag issues on future designs before they compound. The more your team works in CoLab, the smarter it gets and the faster you arrive at the ideal design. Companies like Ford, Komatsu, and Johnson Controls use CoLab to catch issues earlier, eliminate rework cycles, and bring products to market faster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in St. John’s, Newfoundland, CoLab has grown quickly from our first customer in 2019 to a rapidly scaling company. We’ve recently been recognized on Deloitte’s Fast 50™ and Fast 500™, and named a Canadian company to watch by The Globe and Mail and Financial Post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Product Manager on the Build Engineering Reviews team at CoLab, you’ll own one of the most strategically important areas of our platform: how engineering teams collaborate, review designs, and make better decisions together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team sits at the intersection of product strategy, workflow design, and deep technical domain knowledge. You’ll work on the systems and experiences that help mechanical engineering teams run effective design reviews across complex products, stakeholders, and development cycles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You do not need to come from a mechanical engineering background. But you do need the ability — and genuine curiosity — to quickly understand highly technical customer problems and translate them into clear product direction. The engineers and customers you’ll work with are deeply technical. Your job is to bridge that complexity with strong product thinking, prioritization, and execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although you sit within the product organization, you’ll be deeply embedded with a highly technical engineering team. You’ll work closely with engineers, designers, customer-facing teams, and leadership to shape the roadmap, drive alignment, and ensure we’re solving the right problems for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a role where success comes from simply gathering feature requests and writing tickets. You’ll need strong product judgment, comfort operating in ambiguity, and the ability to build trust with people who think deeply about technical systems and workflows every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re energized by difficult product challenges, curious about how complex products get designed and built, and excited about shaping software used by some of the world’s leading engineering organizations, this could be your next role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re an experienced B2B SaaS Product Manager who knows how to navigate complexity, align stakeholders, and ship meaningful products in technical environments. But this role goes beyond owning a roadmap or driving individual initiatives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At CoLab’s stage, we need PMs who actively help level up the product organization itself — shaping how we work, improving product processes, introducing best practices, and raising the bar for cross-functional collaboration and decision making. You won’t succeed here by operating in a silo. The strongest PMs at CoLab are deeply engaged with the broader team and care as much about improving the system around them as they do about delivering their own work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may not be a mechanical engineer — and that’s okay. What matters most is your ability to quickly build domain understanding, ask thoughtful questions, and work effectively with highly technical teams and customers.&lt;/p&gt;
