&lt;p&gt;Our Aerospace &amp;amp; Defense market requires a fundamentally different prospecting approach. Success comes from identifying a small number of highly strategic opportunities and helping organizations navigate complex business priorities, industry initiatives, and government incentives. The goal isn&#39;t to book as many meetings as possible. It&#39;s to help create the next large strategic opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll work in lockstep with an Account Executive, operating as an extension of the account team rather than a standalone outbound rep. Together, you&#39;ll build account plans, map stakeholders, uncover strategic business drivers, and contribute to executive-level business cases that open doors into some of the world&#39;s largest engineering organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is part researcher, part strategist, and part relationship builder. You&#39;ll spend as much time understanding an account&#39;s business priorities as you will prospecting into it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The average person might think this job sounds too hard. If that feels energizing rather than intimidating, you&#39;ll probably thrive here.&lt;/p&gt;
