&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for a high-impact engineering leader who has been in the trenches at fast-scaling startups — someone who has grown from individual contributor to leader and helped scale engineering orgs through multiple phases of growth. Ideally, you&#39;ve done it more than once.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As VP of Software Engineering, you&#39;ll be responsible for building and maintaining a high-performing, scalable engineering organization across Product Development, Ops, and Technical Support. This is a role for someone who’s hands-on enough to spot an issue in a pull request, and strategic enough to influence long-term roadmap, product vision, and cross-functional priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll partner closely with Product and Design to ship great software faster, with fewer surprises. You&#39;ll also work directly with customers and support our GTM motion, stepping in when technical insight is needed on strategic deals or customer challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve helped scale at least one startup through a period of fast growth (Series A → C or similar), and ideally done it more than once.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve grown from IC to leadership, and know what it takes to help others do the same.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re low ego, high respect. People seek out your input not because of your title, but because you are good at what you do, genuinely helpful and motivating to work with.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re a builder at heart — pragmatic, resourceful, and relentlessly focused on outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
